CNMV clarified that the offer is aimed at acquiring 550.008 shares of Federica Paternina at a price of 7.65 euros per share, representing 8.95% of the capital of the company, which is made up of 6,142,786 shares accepted for trading on the stock exchanges in Madrid and Bilbao.
He further explained that 5,592,778 million shares had been quashed, which could not be transferred in any way until the tender, which he specified, was set by Federic Paternino in accordance with the provisions of the applicable standards, was closed.
New tools for car valuation
These days, storms and accidents are not just making money from car services.
Every day, thousands of cars that have suffered an insurance event are pulled to a service where the expert has to estimate the damage and the cost of repair.
No insurance event is the same and calculating the cost of parts and labor time can be a long and complex job.
Calculating manually the cost of repair from 20,000 to 30,000 euros including parts and labor can take two or three hours.
However, with the support of new computer tools it would be a matter of minutes
That is why almost 100% of experts use this type of system.
Service providers and solutions for estimating insurance events and maintenance are dedicated to the collection of information that manufacturers provide to them in order to then develop and offer their customers a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, from the American group of Solera is the leading company; 80% of the evaluation is carried out with its products.
Other companies competing in the field of valuation and information-processing tools for the sector are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with data provided by manufacturers is not at all easy.
According to Eduard Vel<0xC3><0xA1>zquez, Audatex’s trade director, they work in Spain with 63 manufacturers and importers, each providing them with information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data for processing is still growing, as more versions, variants and engine solutions have been listed in the last five years than in the previous fifteen years.
As soon as the new vehicle enters the market, these companies will start working.
This is a very hot job, because it is necessary to catalog each of the thousands of parts of the vehicle and determine its price.
In addition, for each model, "intelligent" graphics processing is carried out, where it is possible to "push out" individual parts of tourist cars.
As for the model with massive sales, the work can be done in a week, if the process is very fast.
As for a minority car, it can take three or four months. At present, Audatex has at its disposal complete information about 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
